A devastating 7.8 magnitude earthquake hit Sichuan province, China, causing over 8,700 deaths and widespread destruction.
The Chinese government allocated 200 million yuan for relief efforts, with international support pouring in.
Russia's President Dmitry Medvedev offered condolences and assistance to China.
Meteorological warnings of heavy rainfall pose challenges to rescue operations, increasing the risk of landslides.
ASEAN countries, including Vietnam, expressed sympathy and support for China.
Germany and Norway pledged financial aid, while Belgium offered 250,000 euros in relief funds.
The State Ethnic Affairs Commission allocated funds to aid ethnic minorities affected by the disaster.
